

 apply string and file manipulation commands


 sed -i 's/<old_word>/<new_world>/g' /path/to/file.txt
 
 update file pass the -i 
 global (find all occurrences) replace g/ means. Without the /g only first occurrence is changed
 To all cases of hello (hello, HELLO, Hello, HEllo, ...) add I ('s/<old_word>/<new_world>/gI')
 s/ for substitute the found expression <old_word> to <new_world>

to delete all lines where there is the word

sudo sed -i '/<word>/d' /home/BSD_DELETE.txt

